<div class="container"><div class="row sMain"><div class="col-md-12" id="SortOrder_56939">
<!-- content Block --><div class="ContentBlock">
<div class="SectionTitleAlt1">About Bad Axe Public Schools</div>
<div class="SectionContent">
<!-- Accordion -->
<div class="panel-group" id="accordion56939" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true">


           <div class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="heading6">
                    <h4 class="panel-title">
                        <a class="collapsed" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion56939" href="#collapse6" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse6">
                            <i class="short-full glyphicon glyphicon-plus"></i>
                            Our Mission
                        </a>
                    </h4>
                </div>
                <div id="collapse6" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="heading6">
                    <div class="panel-body">
                       <div style="text-align: center;">Bad Axe Public Schools is committed to providing quality education for all students to reach their highest potential academically, socially, and physically.</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>



           <div class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="heading7">
                    <h4 class="panel-title">
                        <a class="collapsed" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion56939" href="#collapse7" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse7">
                            <i class="short-full glyphicon glyphicon-plus"></i>
                            Our Vision
                        </a>
                    </h4>
                </div>
                <div id="collapse7" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="heading7">
                    <div class="panel-body">
                       <div style="text-align: center;">Empowering successful learners for today, tomorrow, and the future.</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>



           <div class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="heading8">
                    <h4 class="panel-title">
                        <a class="collapsed" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion56939" href="#collapse8" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse8">
                            <i class="short-full glyphicon glyphicon-plus"></i>
                            Our Community
                        </a>
                    </h4>
                </div>
                <div id="collapse8" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="heading8">
                    <div class="panel-body">
                       <div style="text-align: center;">Bad Axe Public Schools consists of one inclusive campus off of South Van Dyke Road (M-53) on the west side of the city limits of Bad Axe.  The campus has four buildings: High School, Middle School, Elementary School, and Ascent High School.  In addition, the campus has well maintained athletic fields and facilities such as the Claude Marsh Field for football, Turmell Field for baseball, DeCourval Soccer Complex, Lee Kahler Track, Linda &amp; John Rowland Performing Arts Center as well as softball and tennis complexes.</div>

<p style="text-align: center;"> <br>
Bad Axe is a rural community with a population of approximately 3,000. It is the county seat for Huron County located in the Upper "Thumb" of Michigan.  The district encompasses the City of Bad Axe and parts of Verona, Colfax, Meade, Lincoln, Sheridan, and Bingham townships. <br><br>
Within close proximity to the school campus is the Huron Medical Center, Huron Intermediate School District and Technical Center, Huron County Fairgrounds and Ice Arena, Huron County Courthouse, Gemini Group Inc., Huron Daily Tribune, Huron County View, Bad Axe Theatre, WLEW Radio, and a wide variety of shopping, restaurants, and other locally owned businesses.</p>

